><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Computer problems not related to SoL</span><hr size=1> Ok, sorry to tie up the boards with this, but I don't know what to do, and I'm NOT paying $45 an hour to talk to Compaq.  Anyway, here's the specs to the best of my knowledge:<br>
<br>
Compaq Presario 5000A<br>
WindowsME<br>
256 MB ram<br>
10G HD<br>
Xtasy GeForce2 32mb Video Card<br>
Intel Celeron 555 (or something like that)<br>
<br>
I have a Compaq Scanner and Printer connected as well if that makes any difference.<br>
<br>
Ok, I'm going to try and make sense by stating the problem.  <br>
<br>
I have to restart the computer once after I turn it on every time.  If I don't, here's what happens:<br>
<br>
1.  It'll work fine until I connect to the internet and open IE.<br>
2.  I connect to the internet and sign into MSN messenger.<br>
3.  Or start using the computer for very long.  <br>
<br>
What it does is freezes every few seconds.  You can move the mouse and the internet will be working, and then it stops, then it'll go, then it stops. . . non-stop until I reset it.  <br>
<br>
Obviously this is a major pain.  I don't understand why it's doing it.  It's getting very annoying.  Where as I don't have the money to go buy a different brand, I was wondering if anyone might know what is wrong with it.  <br>
<br>
I have had the computer for a little over a year now.  It started doing this about a month or so ago.  I added the video card after it started doing this and the ram and thought maybe (hopefully) that would've taken care of the problem.  It didn't.  <br>
<br>
Anyway, PLEASE help if you can.  Like I said, I can't afford a new computer right now, so that's out.  Any suggestions are welcome!<br>
<br>
Thanks so much!!!<br>
 <p>Janden Furybringer
Lvl 29 Wizard
Metallic Dragons
E'ci</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=milaru>Milaru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/2/02 7:37:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Computer problems not related to SoL</span><hr size=1> Lose ME, I have heard nothing but complaints about it.  98, and 2000 are better products, XP isn't bad if you can force yourself to deal with the fact that it treats you like a 5 year old and has color schemes to match.  (sorry, I dont' use XP, I run 98 and slackware, when I did support it, I found the user interface sucked and the colors were gaudy, which you think I would like)<br>
<br>
Other than that, add some more ram, its cheap, and seemed to help with my problems. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uthreeflies.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThreeFlies</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/2/02 8:19:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Computer problems not related to SoL</span><hr size=1> Comps get cluttered with shareware junk etc, remove everything you dont need/use.<br>
<br>
DEFRAG, Im a defrag addict !<br>
<br>
Add remove programes and choose the repair internet explore' option.<br>
<br>
Im also wondering if maybe your cpu's fan has given-up, slip off the case and see, while your at it get the vacuum with hose attachment on and clean it out, I put the hose against the fans and suck, they spin like crazy and all the fluff is gone.<br>
<br>
I'm sure you'll get a few more ideas to try.<br>
<br>
Good Luck  <br>
<br>
(by the way, I did use win ME and had no problems at all, I now use XP, which is a dream)<br>
<br>
 <p>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jandellon>Jandellon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/2/02 8:30:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Computer problems not related to SoL</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I need to defrag, but it seems to take forever.  I've gone into add/remove programs and into msconfig and gotten rid of everything that I know I don't need.  <br>
<br>
What and where is this &quot;repair internet explorer&quot;?  Never heard of it. . . what does it do, will it take a lot of time to download things off the internet?  I have a dial-up connection.<br>
<br>
Thanks for the responses so far! <p>Janden Furybringer
Lvl 29 Wizard
Metallic Dragons
E'ci</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzilarko.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zilarko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/2/02 8:35:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Computer problems not related to SoL</span><hr size=1> Some suggestions in no particular order:<br>
<br>
Scandisk.<br>
Defrag.<br>
Format c: /u<br>
Load 2000 or 98.<br>
<br>
Know nothing about XP. I have completely avoided it.<br>
Maybe someone can give some advice on the swap file or virtual memory settings, or whatever ME uses.<br>
<br>
And the idea about cleaning the fans is a good idea also.<br>
Clean out all the dust.<br>
Make sure the fans are working.<br>
Maybe even leave the case off and have a floor fan blowing into the case to test for heating problems.<br>
<br>
And I can't end unless I say this:<br>
Get rid of the Compaq. <p>Zilarko<BR>
Gnome Wizard<BR>
Sign of One<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uslimbhcarvul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slimb Hcarvul</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/2/02 9:39:34 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://208.180.232.40/eq/family/images/heads/slimb_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Computer problems not related to SoL</span><hr size=1> If you go into Add/Remove programs, find your Internet Explorer (probably named Microsoft IE 5.0 / 5.5 and internet tools) click on add/remove and you'll get a box with 3 options,  Add a component, repair IE, restore to previous version and possibly  a fourth remove IE.  Now if you have not upgraded IE this option most likely wont be there.   As for your defrag, start it before you go to bed and let it finish that way, I've had a comp or two (not mine fortunately).  Take over 8hrs to defrag ... so just let it go. <p><b><strong>Slimb <br><BR><u>23rd</u> Norse Spiritmaster (Slim)<br><u>9th</U> Briton Friar (Slimb)<BR>
<u>48th</u> Erudite Wizard (Slimb Hcarvul)</strong></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jandellon>Jandellon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/2/02 10:18:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Computer problems not related to SoL</span><hr size=1> Thanks for all the suggestions.  I'll go home and put them all to use! <p>Janden Furybringer
Lvl 29 Wizard
Metallic Dragons
E'ci</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uplexorxteria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Plexor X Teria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/2/02 10:52:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Computer problems not related to SoL</span><hr size=1> One other thing is to make sure you turn off all screen savers and other programs that run periodically, before running scan disk, or it will error out and ask you if you want to start over when your screen saver kicks in.  If none of these suggestions works, then I would definitely suggest reloading the OS.  Windows 98SE should work fine, I run 2000 professional myself.  Whether you reload the OS or not, make sure you have the latest versions of all your drivers, and other patches for the motherboard on up.  <br>
<br>
Last pc I had with chronic crashing/freezing problems was due to overheating, which I determined was caused by using a 16meg video card in a motherboard that was only tested with 8meg cards.  After searching for a long time I found some obscure documentation that told me I needed the next revision of my motherboard to run the 16meg card.  I managed to use that pc for a while, by cranking the ac, and leaving the case open with a fan blowing on it, until I got a new one... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jandellon>Jandellon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/2/02 11:01:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Computer problems not related to SoL</span><hr size=1> The only drivers I know to update are the video and sound.  I go to that Window's Update page and check on that, but that's it.  How do I know what kind of motherboard I have and if I need to get a new driver for it?  Where would I find the driver too?  Just curious.  Are there other drivers other than those that I need to check on updates for?  <br>
<br>
Thanks!!!!! <p>Janden Furybringer
